OL,3,CBenefits crackdown announced by
OL,4,Cgovernment in plan to save #5bn by 2030
OL,6,FThe Work and Pensions Secretary Liz
OL,7,FKendall has outlined radical changes
OL,8,Fto the benefits system to get more
OL,9,Fpeople into work and save #5 billion
OL,10,Fby 2030.
OL,12,FThe changes include scrapping a
OL,13,Fcontroversial benefits assessment, and
OL,14,Ftightening the eligibility criteria
OL,15,Ffor disability benefits.
OL,17,F"Millions of people who could work
OL,18,F(are) trapped on benefits", Kendall
OL,19,Ftold MPs in the House of Commons on
OL,20,FTuesday, insisting the current welfare
OL,21,Fsystem is "holding the country back".
